history.content:
I personally found EE16AB less difficult compared to CS70. CS70 covers an unimaginable amount of material at breathtaking pace, which is not typical of EE16AB. Both of them have weekly problem sets, but they are less difficult than 70 and will probably take lesser time. I guess the addition of 3hr labs could affect your schedule workload but it shouldn't be a burden, I suppose.

CS170, on the other hand, is arguably more challenging than CS70 and will end up taking a lot of your time (in terms of understanding the material; psets should probably take the same time as 70). Though I must acknowledge that it is a much more interesting course and the material covered is absolutely pivotal to a CS curriculum.

Hi, I've taken CS70 and was wondering how EE16A,  EE16B, and CS170 compare in terms of difficulty and time commitment. I did alright in CS70 and probably put in 8 hours into hw with a lot of help at study parties and self work. I've heard CS70 is a difficult class but was curious how other, theory/problem-set classes compare to it.
history.subject: Difficulty of EE16A, EE16B, and CS170 as compared to CS70
